50|$|Solid-state storage (sometimes {{abbreviated}} as SSS) {{is a type}} of <b>non-volatile</b> computer <b>storage</b> that {{stores and}} retrieves digital information using only electronic circuits, without any involvement of moving mechanical parts. This differs fundamentally from the traditional electromechanical storage paradigm, which accesses data using rotating or linearly moving media coated with magnetic material.|$|R
