5000|$|The [...] "R" [...] format DVDs can {{be written}} once and read {{arbitrarily}} many times. Thus, [...] "R" [...] format discs are suited to applications such as <b>non-volatile</b> data <b>storage,</b> audio, or video. This can cause confusion because the DVD+RW Alliance logo is a stylized 'RW'. Thus, a DVD+R disc may have the RW logo, {{but it is not}} rewritable.|$|R
